 bottom up, identifying the links between the varying importance of sexuality as a movement theme and actors' mobilization, and enhances the import of subjectivity in militancy. It draws attention to cultural, sometimes infrapolitical, forms of militancy that perpetuate the role of sexuality in LGBTQ militancy.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 4aConflict and Peace. 4aContemporary Society. 4aGender Studies. 4aSocial and Political Sciences. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Minority Studies.2bisacsh  aHomosexualities and LGBTQ militancy, Sexuality, Social movements, Sociology, Subjectivity.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311066152108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDTL Humanities 2020z978311073776908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Economics, Law & Social Sciences 2019 ENGz978311061013008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2019z9783110606485oZDB-23-DSW40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789048528646zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789048528646423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9789048528646.jpg  a978-3-11-061013-0  EBOOK PACKAGE Economics, Law & Social Sciences 2019 ENGb2019  a978-3-11-061076-5  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-066152-1  Amsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  a978-3-11-073776-9  DTL Humanities 2020b2020  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-al